# NOOP Steps Guide

NOOP (No Operation) steps are useful for testing workflows and creating manual trigger points.

### Basic NOOP Step
```typescript
import { NoopConfig } from 'motia'

export const config: NoopConfig = {
  type: 'noop',                    // ✅ REQUIRED: Step type
  name: 'ManualTrigger',          // ✅ REQUIRED: Unique identifier
  description: 'Manual trigger point for workflow',  // ✅ OPTIONAL: Description
  virtualEmits: ['workflow.start'],      // ✅ REQUIRED: Virtual topic emissions
  virtualSubscribes: ['manual.trigger'], // ✅ REQUIRED: Virtual topic subscriptions
  flows: ['my-workflow']                 // ✅ REQUIRED: Flow association
}

// ✅ IMPORTANT: NOOP steps have NO handler - they're for workflow visualization only
```

### UI Trigger NOOP (for UI Steps)
```typescript
// For interactive UI components that trigger API calls
export const config: NoopConfig = {
  type: 'noop',
  name: 'ButtonTrigger',
  description: 'UI button that triggers API endpoints',
  virtualSubscribes: [],                    // ✅ REQUIRED: Empty array for UI triggers
  virtualEmits: [
    {
      topic: '/api/button-action',          // ✅ Must match API step path exactly
      label: 'Button clicked action'
    }
  ],
  flows: ['ui-workflow']
}
```

